Mario Mandzukic took a step closer to leaving Bayern Munich today when he was left out of Pep Guardiola's squad for the German Cup final.

The 27-year-old Croat is wanted by Arsenal, Chelsea and Real Madrid but Guardiola has dropped him, allegedly for disciplinary reasons.

Mandzukic has played a key role for the Bavarians this season, scoring 26 goals in all competitions but also clashed with Guardiola in January when he was excluded from the team.

