'He was injured, but on the other hand he actually was able to play,' Guardiola said cryptically.

'But I decided to take 18 players with me. And Mandzukic is not in the squad.'

The Bundesliga champions were initially reluctant to sell Mandzukic despite Robert Lewandowski arriving next season from Saturday's opponents Borussia Dortmund but now they are willing to listen to offers.

Arsenal have made enquiries to ascertain the scale of the fee and wages while Chelsea want him as a second striker to support and cover Diego Costa.

Guardiola wants Chelsea's £30m-rated defender David Luiz and could be willing to agree a compromise deal with Mandzukic, also valued at £30m, going the other way but the Croat is keen to play regularly rather than be a secondary figure.

